@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - marketplace/AcceptedAgreement
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired AcceptedAgreement spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetAcceptedAgreement;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListAcceptedAgreements using filters\nagreement_id, compartment_id, display_name,\nlisting_id (+1 more);
:Create the OCI resource via\nCreateAcceptedAgreement when no reusable match\nis found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteAcceptedAgreement with\nrequired via GetAcceptedAgreement or\nListAcceptedAgreements to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetAcceptedAgreement or\nListAcceptedAgreements until OCI reaches\nDELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields agreement_id, compartment_id,\nlisting_id, package_version (+1 more);
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateAcceptedAgreement only for mutable\nfields defined_tags, display_name,\nfreeform_tags;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: marketplace
slug: acceptedagreement
kind: AcceptedAgreement
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: defined_tags, display_name,
freeform_tags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
agreement_id, compartment_id, listing_id,
package_version (+1 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_marketplace_accepted_agreements
filters agreement_id, compartment_id,
display_name, listing_id (+1 more)
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
AcceptedAgreement reuses an existing OCI
agreement before create by exact compartmentId,
listingId, packageVersion, and agreementId
match, with displayName narrowing when set.
OCI accepted agreement responses do not expose
lifecycle state, so successful create and update
normalize directly to Active from the immediate
response body.
In-place updates are limited to displayName,
definedTags, and freeformTags; agreementId,
compartmentId, listingId, packageVersion, and
signature are replacement-only.
The controller mirrors the last applied
signature at status.appliedSignature because OCI
read models never return the signature needed
for explicit drift checks.
Delete retains the finalizer until
DeleteAcceptedAgreement is followed by
GetAcceptedAgreement returning not found.
end note
@enduml
